Boolean expression details: In independent experiments cebpa and mitf1 were found to be positive (PMID:2006196) and negative regulators (PMID:23871207).
stat5 phosphorylation causes cebpb-mediated transcriptional activation of cebpb targets (PMID:12574125).
cebpa blocks transcriptional activation function of cjun TF (PMC139872).
Induction of pu1 promotes egr expression but gfi1 binds to egr regulatory sequences and keep it inactive (PMID:16923394).
cebpa promotes gfi1 expression but egr2 binds to egr regulatory sequences and keep it inactive (PMID:16923394).
gata1 directly binds to its own regulatory sequences and promotes its expression (PMID:2044960; PMID21571218).
gata2 and gata1 binds and activates gata2 promoter (PMID12857954; PMID15494394). Independently, stimulation of stat5 forces gata2 expression (PMID:25801432).
cebpa directly binds regulatory sequences of mitf and maintain inactive (PMID:23871207). In an independent experiment induced ckit phosphorilation force mitf expression (PMC1858054)

Independently, it has been shown that pu1 (PMID:7478579), runx1 (PMID:17994017) and cebpa in combination with cjun (PMID:18026136) are positive pu1 regulators. Finally, if gfi1 is induced pu1 is downregulated (PMID:19818654).
All gata2, pu1 and runx1 binds to a runx1 and activates enhancer (PMID:17823307; PMID21571218).
In independent experiments cebpa (PMID:18550858) and pu1 (PMID:9292515) were found to be negative regulators of cmyb.
gata1 is a positive regulator of scl but only in combination of scl (PMID:17709394).
il3ra gene has gata binding regions in its promoter (PMID:7858255)
jak2 phosporylates stat5 and promotes its trancriptional activity function (PMID:9575217:PMID:9363920)
il3ra and gmcsfr are receptors that binds independently to respective cytokines and activates jak-stat signaling by binding to bc subunit (PMID:22257375).
Systematical deletion of cebpa and pu1 binding regions reveals that both are necessary to bc activation (PMID: 10453008)

Logic function: ( ( pu1 & runx1 ) | ( pu1 & cjun ) ) & ! ( gata1 | gata2 )
Boolean expression details: pu1 and runx1 synergize to activate mcsfr gene (PMID:21518930). Independently, cjun and pu1 activates mcsfr expression (PMID:9988737), but this is disrupted when gata factors are present (PMID:8264604)
pu1 and runx1 sinergize to activate gmcsfr gene expression (PMID:21518930).
cebpa and pu1 directly binds and activates regulatory sequences of gcsfr gene (PMID:8695841;  PMID:9632814).

Logic function: ( cebpa | cmyb ) & pu1 & ! egr & ! ( gata1 | gata2 )
Boolean expression details: Expression of cebpa or cmyb promotes ne promoter activation but only when pu1 is present (PMID:8756629). When, the three factors  are present they sinergize. Lack of function egr mutants overexpressed neutrophil markers as ne (PMID:16923394). gata factors promotes basophil or eosinophil differentiation vs neutrophil formation (PMID:17079688).

pu1 and cebpa in concert activate mpo expression (PMID:17079688). egr downregulates expression of neutrophil markers (PMID:16923394). gata factors promotes basophil or eosinophil differentiation vs neutrophil formation (PMID:17079688)

cebpa activates lf gene promoter (PMID:12522000). egr downregulates expression of neutrophil markers (16923394). gata factors promotes basophil or eosinophil differentiation vs neutrophil formation (PMID:17079688)

Logic function: ( ( cebpa | cebpb ) & ( gata1 | gata2 ) & pu1 ) & !  ( gfi1 & gcsfr )
Boolean expression details: cebp and gata factors sinyergize with pu1 to activate mbp gene (PMID:12202480). Independently, gfi1 inhibits mbp during gcsfr stimulation (PMID:22552881).
mitf pathway activated by ckit stimulation causes mmcp6 expression (PMID:8839840). cjun synergizes with mitf to activate mmcp6 transcription (PMID:15464728)
gata2 directly binds regulatory sequences and activates mccpa gene transcription (PMID:1744088). ckit-mitf1 signaling activates mccpa activation (PMID:1744088).
gata1 is an positive regulator of ckit gene but only in the presence of scl (PMID:19011221). Independently, gata2 activates ckit gene (PMID:20833840).  ckit transactivates ckit promoter (PMC1858054).
gata1 binds regulatory sequences of fceRIb gene and activates its expression (PMID:16522818)
gata factors directly binds and positively regulates regulatory sequences of the fceRIa gene (PMID:15967781).
gata1, pu1 and runx1 directly binds regulatory sequences of ccr3 gene (PMID21041734; PMID:27340386). cebpa is a major TF required to the expression of eosinophil markers (PMID:17079688).
